-- rates-service seed data (L1). Synthetic, modeled on real freight structure
-- (magnitudes: docs/domain-notes.md). NOT schema — applied by `make seed` via
-- `docker compose exec -T rates-db psql`, never by Flyway.
--
-- Idempotent by construction: every row has a FIXED UUID and every INSERT uses
-- ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING, so re-running seeds nothing new and never renumbers
-- IDs. This protects cross-service FK-by-convention (booking.quotes.lane_id /
-- rate_card_id reference these IDs with no hard FK — see MASTER_PLAN §4.2).
-- Tradeoff (accepted at L1): editing a magnitude below does NOT update an existing
-- row; to change seed values, `make down` (drops the volume) then `make up && make seed`.
--
-- UUID scheme:  lanes 1111…-NN   rate_cards 2222…-NN   surcharges 3333…-NN
-- Money: base_rate_cents = cents-per-container (ocean), cents-per-kg (air), or
-- cents-per-mile (truck); surcharges.amount = cents when FLAT, basis points when PERCENT.

BEGIN;

